      "text": "A patient is brought to the emergency department with signs suggest opioid poisoning. What is the antidote of choice?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Flumazenil"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Atropine"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Naloxone"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Physostigmine"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Option C - Naloxone</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Naloxone</strong> is the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e22dbf6c52169277719441ac94a69e\">opioid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2e432a4f3c1692777181e8e244ca0e\">antagonist</span> that rapidly reverses opioid-induced <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> depression and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cacca0f20e169277719222049c80a2\">miosis</span> — it is the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5e612ce1381692777181adc76f11e6\">antidote</span> of choice in suspected <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e22dbf6c52169277719441ac94a69e\">opioid</span> overdose.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Opioid Overdose/ Poisoning</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Cause</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Clinical, accidental, or suicidal overdose.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Symptoms</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Unconsiousness/coma</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Miosis: Pin point pupil</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Respiratory depression</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Dry <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9b0ae3750916927771986c15d4ff4d\">secretion</span> in the eye/mouth</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Urinary retention</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Constipation</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Flaccid muscles</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Convulsions (in children)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Management</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Acute overdose/poisoning:</strong> IV Naloxone (Antidote)</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>                            ↓</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Maintenance</strong> (Detoxification phase: To prevent withdrawal):</p>\n\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Opioids: Buprenorphine, Methadone, Tramadol</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Non-Opioids- Clonidine, Lofexidine</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\n\t\t\t<p>                            ↓</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Abstinence</strong> (Prevent relapse):</p>\n\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>DOC: Oral Naltrexone</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Flumazenil (Option A):</strong> Antagonizes benzodiazepines, not opioids.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Atropine (Option B): </strong>Anticholinergic agent - not the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5e612ce1381692777181adc76f11e6\">antidote</span> for opioids.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Physostigmine (Option D):</strong> For <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9b4dbbb3321692777181e6fe172b88\">anticholinergic</span> overdose; not for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e22dbf6c52169277719441ac94a69e\">opioid</span> toxicity.</li>\n</ul>",
